<font color="#FF0000">SHARE THE MISERY</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 25 18:52:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
You were born in 1964.  I was drafted in 1964.  I went to Vietnam with an artillery unit and got out of the army in 1966.  I did not realize there were so many people against the Vietnam war until I got back.  I was just trying to keep my head down and get back in one piece.  I managed to do that, thank God!  I was just trying to figure out why we were there in the first place and wondering why Muhammed Ali (Casius Clay) wasn't over here with us.  I was miserable over there and wanted other people share my misery. I thought we were there fighting communism and their thoughts of world domination.  
